comments: Snell (DET) makes contact to Rubio's (PHX) body during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Hall (DET) extends into Booker's (PHX) path and delivers contact during the screen.
Wood (DET) makes contact with Booker's (PHX) shot attempt after it hits the backboard and still has a chance to score.
Snell (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bridges (PHX) and absorbs the contact.
Ayton's (PHX) arm is extended in Wood's (DET) path but the contact is marginal and does not affect his FOM.
Johnson (PHX) makes marginal contact with Rose (DET) as he firms up during the pick.
Rose (DET) places a legal arm to the front of Rubio (PHX) during his drive to the basket.
Booker (PHX) takes a step with his pivot foot prior to the release of his jump shot attempt.
Galloway (DET) is in a legal defensive position and the marginal contact is created by Booker (PHX).
Booker (PHX) briefly places his arm around Galloway's (DET) front, but does not affect his FOM.
Rubio (PHX) is established in a screening position in Snell's (DET) path and the contact between the two players is marginal.
Snell (DET) jumps to the side of Booker (PHX) and would avoid making contact with him if Booker did not extend his arm to create the marginal contact.
